This paper belongs to the field of natural language processing and artificial intelligence, as it focuses on the development and testing of intelligent conversational agents or chatbots. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. 

The paper also discusses the ethical implications of persuasive chatbots, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction and computer ethics, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) likely sub-categories as well. 

Finally, the study involves a large-scale online experiment, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it involves the analysis of social interactions and the use of online platforms.
